
25. Explain how SonarLint helps in code quality.

SonarLint is a static code analysis tool that detects issues while writing code.

What SonarLint Detects:

    Bugs

    Code smells

    Security vulnerabilities

    Duplicated code

    Poor coding practices

Uses:

    Real-time feedback in IDE

    Improves maintainability

    Enforces coding standards

    Reduces technical debt

    Helps write clean, readable code